JS
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BASICS
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    let , var | can defined or redefined many times
    const     | constants can assign variable once

Function declarations
    function add(num1, num2) {
      return num1 + num2;
    }
    
    add(1, 3);
    => 4

Export & Import
    export const MY_VALUE = 10;
    
    export function add(num1, num2) {
      return num1 + num2;
    }
    
    import { MY_VALUE, add } from './file';
    
    add(MY_VALUE, 5);
    => 15
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ARITHMETRIC OPERATORS
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ARITHMETRIC OPERATORS & ShortHand Assignment Operators
    addition    |     +     |     +=
    subtract    |     -     |     -=
    multiply    |     *     |     *=
    divide      |     /     |     /=
    remaining   |     %     |     %=
    power       |     **    |     **=

Order of Operations
result = 3 ** 3 + 9 * 4 / (3 - 1);
    => 3 ** 3 + 9 * 4/2
    => 27 + 9 * 4/2
    => 27 + 18
    => 45
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
STRING INT BOOLEAN
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
>string
    \n  | new line
    'string'[index]
    'string'.charAt(index)
    'string'.length , .toUpperCase() , .toLowerCase() , .trim() , etc.
    string is immutable can't change from the original form
    string can joint with + (plus sign)
>int
>boolean
    true , false
    ||  (disjuction)  or
    &&  (conjuction)  and
    !   (negation)    not
    using () for higher precedence
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
COMPARITION
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
a > b     |    Greater than	
a >= b    |    Greater than or equals	
a < b     |    Less than	
a <= b    |    Less than or equals	
a === b   |    (Strict) Equals	
a !== b   |    Not (strict) equals	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ARRAY
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
> called the array
    array;
> called element in the array
    array[index];
> declared new element in the array
    array[index] = newValue;
> added or removed to the end
    - push(value)
    - pop()
> added or removed to the first
    - unshift(value)
    - shift()
> specific index can be added or removed or replaced
    - splice(indexStart , indexEnd , value)
        add     | array.splice(position , deleteTime = 0 , newValue)
        remove  | array.splice(position , deleteTimes);
        replace | array.splice(position = 1 , deleteTime = 1 , newValue); for replace 1 element
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
> build-in
    getItem([array] , position)                   | retrieve
    setItem([array] , position , replacementCard) | exchange
    insertItemAtTop([array , newCard])            | insert at the top of the stack
    removeItem([array] , position)                | remove
    removeItemFromTop([array])                    | remove from the top of the stack
    insertItemAtBottom([array] , newCard)         | insert at the bottom of the stack
    removeItemAtBottm([array])                    | remove from the bottom of the stack
    checkSizeOfStack([array] , stackSize)         | check is equal to stackSize or not
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
